# .gcloudignore — controls what `gcloud ... --source` uploads as the build context.
#
# `gcloud run deploy --source` builds with Cloud buildpacks (functions-framework via
# --function=Expense) because there is no file named `Dockerfile` at the root — the
# dev image is `Dockerfile.dev`, which gcloud does not auto-detect. This file just
# keeps secrets and dev/infra noise out of the uploaded build context.
#
# NOTE: when this file exists, gcloud does NOT also apply .gitignore — so secrets and
# local-only files must be listed here explicitly.

# Dev container — never built in the cloud (buildpacks are used instead).
Dockerfile.dev
docker-compose.yml

# Secrets / local env — never upload into a build context.
.env
*.crt
debug.go

# VCS & tooling.
.git/
.gitignore
.github/
.vscode/

# Infra / docs — not needed to build the app.
terraform/
docs/
*.md

# Build artifacts.
main
*.exe
*.exe~
